; UTILITY: slow LFO — two slow ramps drifting in and out of phase; `rephase` sets the drift rate.
; A 1 Hz phasor divided by 20 gives a 20 s ramp (fractional Hz is not representable);
; :b drifts its divided phase against :a so the pair slide past each other.
(def slow-lfo (fn (:rephase => :a :b)
  (def osc (phasor :hz 1))
  (<- a (follow osc :div 20))
  (<- b (follow osc :div 20 :drift rephase))))
